        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40671",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "For me both filters are working also on german umlauts or accedent characters. This is even unittested.\r\n\r\nCan you give an reproduceable example of your problem?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-24T13:54:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-24T13:54:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40673",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Flavio\r\n\r\nTry assign encoding.\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n$filter = new Zend_Filter_StringToUpper('UTF-8');\r\necho $filter->filter('a\u00e7\u00e3o');\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-24T15:34:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-24T15:34:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40674",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fgsl",
                        "name": "fgsl",
                        "displayName": "Fl\u00e1vio Gomes da Silva Lisboa",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Aswering to Thomas Weidner, the example can be made into an indexAction() so:\r\n\r\npublic function indexAction()\r\n{\r\n    $filter = new Zend_Filter_StringToUpper();\r\n    echo $filter->filter('a\u00e7\u00e3o');\r\n    exit;\r\n}\r\n\r\nThe response will be \"A\u00e7\u00e3O\".\r\n\r\nHowever, I follow the guideline of Ramon Henrique Ornelas and change the code to:\r\n\r\npublic function indexAction()\r\n{\r\n    $filter = new Zend_Filter_StringToUpper('UTF-8');\r\n    echo $filter->filter('a\u00e7\u00e3o');\r\n    exit;\r\n}\r\n\r\nSetting the encoding of browser to UTF-8, the response was \"A\u00c7\u00c3O\".\r\n\r\nSo... that is not a bug... excuse me, and thank you at same time.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fgsl",
                        "name": "fgsl",
                        "displayName": "Fl\u00e1vio Gomes da Silva Lisboa",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-24T17:12:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-24T17:12:18.000+0000"
                },
